{{Infobox MMA event|name=Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship: Art of War 2|image=|promotion=[[Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship]]|date=May 11, 2007|venue=[[American Airlines Center]]|city=[[Austin, Texas|Austin]], [[Texas]]|attendance=2,854<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/articles/Guillen-Tops-Sims-Loiseau-Earns-Win-7526|title=– GUILLEN DEFEATS SIM ON "ART OF WAR" SHOW - SHERDOG.com|website=www.sherdog.com}}</ref>|gate=|buyrate=|previousevent=[[Art of War 1]]|followingevent=[[Art of War 3]]}}

'''''Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship: Art of War 2''''' was the second [[mixed martial arts]] event by the mixed martial arts organization [[Art of War Undisputed Arena Fighting Championship]]. The event took place on Saturday, May 11, 2007<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://onthemat.com/art-of-war-2-mixed-martial-arts-fighting-set-for-austin-conv-center-may-11/|title=ART OF WAR 2, MIXED-MARTIAL ARTS FIGHTING SET FOR AUSTIN CONV. CENTER, MAY 11|access-date=2018-02-21}}</ref> at the [[Austin Convention Center]] in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]], [[Texas]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/sports/2007-05-10/473502/|title=Art of War 2 Invades Convention Center|access-date=2018-02-21|language=en-US}}</ref>  The card aired on [[HDTV]].

== History ==
The fight card included Chris Guillen and [[Wes Sims (fighter)|Wes Sims]] in the main event.  The show also featured a bout between [[David Loiseau]] and Freddie Espircueta.

